opml.py has some command-line options

You should be able to get started with:

mkdir -p ~/ENV/keepup
virtualenv ~/ENV/keepup
source ~/ENV/keepup/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
opml.py --help

Then you also need to create twitter API credentials. 


Working on flask stuff based off of this tutorial: 
http://blog.miguelgrinberg.com/post/the-flask-mega-tutorial-part-i-hello-world
